        "text": "Each year the Indianapolis Bar Foundation honors individuals for their dedication to the law by bestowing on them the designation of Distinguished Fellow. In addition, designation of Distinguished Life Fellow is bestowed upon individuals who have continued to show their dedication to the law over their extensive careers. These small but select groups are chosen by the Directors of the Indianapolis Bar Foundation each year to become Distinguished Fellows and Distinguished Life Fellows as a result of their significant contributions to the legal profession and to the Indianapolis community. Nominated by a committee of Bar Foundation board members and active contributors, Beth Green was recognized as part of this year’s Class of Distinguished Fellows. Tony Jost was recognized a Distinguished Life Fellow. The awards were presented at the Indianapolis Bar Association/Indianapolis Bar Foundation Recognition Breakfast on November 21, 2017."
